<item>
            <title>[LU-670] Remove ldiskfs_dirhash from Lustre</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-670</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ldiskfs_dirhash() function is only used by the ldiskfs osd.  Since this functionality was originally copied from ldiskfs it makes sense to remove it entirely and rely on the ldiskfs implementation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Normally this symbol isn&apos;t exported but since we are already patching ldiskfs exporting it for use is trivial.  This is currently done with the following ldiskfs patch for rhel6.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  ldiskfs/kernel_patches/patches/ext4-osd-iam-exports-rhel6.patch&lt;/p&gt;</description>
